WEBVTT

00:42.542 --> 00:45.962
SOLD OUT ON YOU

00:50.800 --> 00:51.760
Do you want perfection?

00:53.595 --> 00:55.597
Then, don't stand by my side.

00:55.680 --> 00:56.723
Do you want perfection?

00:56.806 --> 00:58.516
Then, don't stand by my side.

00:58.600 --> 00:59.517
INSTANT CURRY

00:59.601 --> 01:01.352
Say "Ah."

01:01.436 --> 01:02.353
It's so delicious.

01:02.437 --> 01:04.856
No need to worry about tonight's dinner!

01:04.939 --> 01:06.983
No need to worry about tonight's dinner!

01:08.151 --> 01:09.152
EUNSUNG SUPER VACUUM

01:10.528 --> 01:12.447
-You're a lifesaver.
-You're a lifesaver.

01:37.222 --> 01:38.473
Mom…

01:38.556 --> 01:39.432
Ye-jin!

01:40.433 --> 01:43.144
Ye-jin, are you okay? Are you hurt?

01:43.853 --> 01:44.979
Mom…

01:47.816 --> 01:49.359
Dad,

01:49.442 --> 01:51.945
this person is my mom, right?

01:53.196 --> 01:54.322
Is it?

01:54.405 --> 01:56.950
Is she really my mom?

01:58.910 --> 01:59.911
Mom!

01:59.994 --> 02:01.913
It's me, Dam Seok-gyeong.

02:01.996 --> 02:04.541
Ye-jin's having a hard time.

02:04.624 --> 02:06.042
Can you meet her just once?

02:13.299 --> 02:14.551
Ye-jin.

02:17.137 --> 02:18.179
It's me, your mom.

02:19.222 --> 02:20.140
Come here.

02:24.060 --> 02:25.562
Mom!

02:29.232 --> 02:32.777
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

02:45.081 --> 02:46.791
-How is it? Is it good?
-It's good.

03:11.107 --> 03:12.150
Mom.

03:13.484 --> 03:17.196
Can't we play outside next time?

03:18.448 --> 03:19.324
What?

03:20.199 --> 03:23.411
I want to go
to an amusement park with you.

03:24.746 --> 03:25.747
Well…

03:26.623 --> 03:28.583
-I'm really busy--
-Then…

03:29.667 --> 03:31.711
When can I see you again?

03:40.470 --> 03:41.471
Ye-jin.

03:42.013 --> 03:44.015
This is my number.

03:44.641 --> 03:47.101
You can call me at this number
when you miss me.

03:47.602 --> 03:48.436
Really?

03:48.519 --> 03:53.066
But can you promise me
just one thing in return?

03:53.900 --> 03:56.986
Until I come to see you,

03:57.904 --> 04:00.615
promise to never come looking for me.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.207
Because--

04:09.290 --> 04:11.084
Because it's our secret.

04:19.842 --> 04:21.928
Can I call you every day?

04:23.346 --> 04:25.390
Right, you're busy.

04:26.724 --> 04:29.602
Then, how about this?

04:30.144 --> 04:32.397
Every Sunday night at 8:00 p.m.,

04:32.480 --> 04:35.817
no matter how busy I am,
I promise to pick up.

04:35.900 --> 04:37.485
Hey, Ye-jin.

04:37.568 --> 04:40.780
Mom, I became class president!
Everyone except three people voted for me.

04:41.906 --> 04:42.949
Congratulations!

04:51.791 --> 04:53.960
EUN-SU'S LAW

04:54.043 --> 04:57.755
COMMENT
SONG MYEONG-HWA'S ACTING IS AMAZING!

04:58.840 --> 05:00.133
MOM

05:02.093 --> 05:04.095
Mom, do you finally get
your revenge tomorrow?

05:04.721 --> 05:06.055
Can't you tell just me?

05:06.139 --> 05:08.349
It's more fun if you watch it yourself.

05:09.851 --> 05:10.893
Ms. Song.

05:11.394 --> 05:12.353
They need me.

05:12.937 --> 05:15.273
-Let's talk more next week.
-Okay.

05:15.356 --> 05:16.441
I love you--

05:26.242 --> 05:28.786
The person you are calling is unavailable.

05:34.709 --> 05:37.962
-Gosh, Song Myeong-hwa got in an accident.
-Really? What happened?

05:43.259 --> 05:45.428
SONG MYEONG-HWA
IN CRITICAL CONDITION AFTER CAR CRASH

06:03.154 --> 06:05.198
Correct that false report first.

06:05.281 --> 06:07.033
-Ms. Song Myeong-hwa!
-Ms. Song Myeong-hwa!

06:07.116 --> 06:08.701
How did the accident occur?

06:08.785 --> 06:10.161
What happened to the others?

06:10.244 --> 06:11.162
Mom!

06:15.917 --> 06:17.251
Do you know this kid?

06:21.214 --> 06:22.256
I mean…

06:22.340 --> 06:23.925
You can't just let anyone in here!

06:25.301 --> 06:27.386
Sorry. She needs to rest right now.

06:31.390 --> 06:33.559
-Please leave right now!
-Song Myeong-hwa!

06:34.602 --> 06:37.021
Mom, I'm sorry.

06:38.064 --> 06:40.233
Please, just pick up.

06:43.236 --> 06:45.446
Mom, please answer the phone.

06:47.698 --> 06:48.533
Just once…

06:48.616 --> 06:51.577
The person you are calling is unavailable.
Please leave a message…

06:51.661 --> 06:52.995
Just once…

06:54.080 --> 06:55.081
Mom.

06:57.667 --> 06:59.544
Why weren't you picking up?

07:12.473 --> 07:14.016
Are you listening?

07:18.771 --> 07:20.356
You've called the wrong number.

07:27.405 --> 07:28.656
Hello?

07:30.450 --> 07:31.576
Hello?

07:58.978 --> 08:00.062
Mom?

08:02.148 --> 08:04.358
-Mom.
-If you call me one more time,

08:04.442 --> 08:06.277
I'm going to call the cops.

08:06.360 --> 08:07.904
This is my last warning.

08:52.281 --> 08:53.950
-Look here.
-I miss you.

08:59.121 --> 09:00.915
I miss you,

09:03.292 --> 09:04.418
Mom.

10:00.224 --> 10:01.100
SOM'S VARIETY SHOP

10:01.183 --> 10:02.268
Jin-yi!

10:02.351 --> 10:05.855
It seems our regulars
are here early this morning.

10:05.938 --> 10:08.024
Hey, Jin-yi. My stool, please.

10:08.107 --> 10:10.943
-A stool for me too.
-Your stools!

10:11.569 --> 10:12.612
All right.

10:12.695 --> 10:15.573
-A high one for you.
-A high one.

10:15.656 --> 10:17.825
And a low one for you.

10:17.908 --> 10:19.118
Thank you.

10:19.201 --> 10:21.662
Don't share these
just because you're friends, okay?

10:21.746 --> 10:25.082
You need to use the right ones
for your heights to protect your knees.

10:26.417 --> 10:28.461
I want to buy a stool too.

10:29.211 --> 10:31.088
Let me hear Jin-yi nag about my knees.

10:31.839 --> 10:34.091
There's no need to buy one.

10:34.175 --> 10:36.927
-Just give me one.
-Save your money.

10:37.678 --> 10:39.180
She's so considerate.

10:39.263 --> 10:41.849
Jin-yi is a true businesswoman.

10:41.932 --> 10:43.351
"The Cunning Dealer Jin-yi."

10:44.101 --> 10:46.270
-All right, let's go.
-Let's go.

10:46.354 --> 10:47.897
-We have to go now.
-Bye.

10:47.980 --> 10:51.275
-Let's go have some coffee.
-Let's go get coffee.

10:51.359 --> 10:52.193
Hey, Som-yi!

10:52.276 --> 10:54.570
Hang on! Come here.

10:55.821 --> 10:56.864
I don't want to.

10:57.531 --> 10:59.450
Let me see…

11:01.118 --> 11:01.994
All right.

11:02.536 --> 11:03.371
Wear this.

11:04.455 --> 11:05.498
What is this?

11:05.581 --> 11:09.502
It's a Punggi rayon mask
that I got just for you.

11:09.585 --> 11:11.545
It doesn't trap sweat,
and it's very breathable.

11:11.629 --> 11:13.255
It's so soft. Isn't it awesome?

11:13.339 --> 11:15.508
Forget it. I'll stick with what I have.

11:16.175 --> 11:19.387
Five, four, three!

11:20.012 --> 11:21.389
Come on!

11:30.272 --> 11:31.107
What do you think?

11:33.442 --> 11:34.402
It's so-so.

11:36.195 --> 11:37.613
Na Som-yi.

11:43.953 --> 11:45.079
No way!

11:45.162 --> 11:47.957
Jin-yi, this is what I really wanted!

11:48.040 --> 11:50.459
What kind of angel left this here for me?

11:50.543 --> 11:53.587
Who else would it be?
You begged Mechoori for it, didn't you?

11:54.380 --> 11:55.297
No, I didn't.

11:55.381 --> 11:58.717
I'm going to open this later,
so keep it safe for me.

12:02.471 --> 12:03.305
You're doing great.

12:35.546 --> 12:37.214
My eyes are a bit puffy.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.800
Did I eat too much soup last night?

12:43.971 --> 12:44.805
Goodness.

12:48.184 --> 12:49.268
Are you leaving?

12:49.351 --> 12:51.353
Yes. Are you heading out too?

12:51.437 --> 12:53.522
-Yeah, I'm going to the market.
-I see.

12:53.606 --> 12:55.858
Let's go together. I'm riding the bus too.

12:55.941 --> 12:57.568
Sure. I'll give you a ride there.

12:58.152 --> 13:00.946
-You drive?
-Of course not.

13:01.030 --> 13:04.492
There's someone who never lets me walk.

13:23.719 --> 13:25.763
Yeah, that's the one!

13:25.846 --> 13:29.475
This chicken was flying
like an eagle yesterday!

13:29.558 --> 13:30.893
You…

13:30.976 --> 13:33.854
You treated me like a thief
and even called the cops.

13:34.897 --> 13:38.025
But is that really a chicken though?

13:38.692 --> 13:40.528
I'm telling you, it's really weird.

13:45.491 --> 13:47.368
You don't have anything to say to me?

13:54.041 --> 13:55.251
Here.

14:02.299 --> 14:04.176
I wasn't asking for repair costs.
An apology--

14:04.260 --> 14:05.469
We're all done, right?

14:06.053 --> 14:08.097
I hope we don't cross paths again.

14:10.057 --> 14:11.559
Excuse me!

14:11.642 --> 14:12.810
What? What is it now?

14:14.353 --> 14:15.354
Let's talk.

14:16.814 --> 14:19.567
We're going to miss the bus! Let's go.

14:28.158 --> 14:30.411
You can't take out any of this stuff?

14:30.494 --> 14:32.913
No. I only have space to give you a ride.

14:34.290 --> 14:37.418
Then, she can sit on my lap.

14:37.501 --> 14:38.919
You got knee surgery last year.

14:39.003 --> 14:39.920
You can't do that.

14:41.130 --> 14:42.214
You should get on, ma'am.

14:42.298 --> 14:43.257
I'll just walk.

14:43.340 --> 14:44.842
Why don't you come with us?

14:44.925 --> 14:45.885
We're going to be late.

14:47.511 --> 14:49.096
My goodness.

14:53.350 --> 14:54.310
Just sit.

14:56.395 --> 14:58.272
You look so good together.

14:58.355 --> 15:01.275
-Darling, do you have a boyfriend?
-Pardon?

15:01.358 --> 15:02.776
Ma'am!

15:02.860 --> 15:06.488
Gosh, my knees hurt. I better sit down.

15:12.995 --> 15:14.330
Put your feet up.

15:16.999 --> 15:18.000
Okay.

15:35.392 --> 15:36.977
Oh, my gosh!

15:37.061 --> 15:39.355
Bees! Mister, there are bees over here!

15:39.438 --> 15:40.481
Are they gone yet?

15:40.564 --> 15:42.107
Are they gone?

15:42.191 --> 15:43.317
They're gone.

15:48.822 --> 15:50.199
Why were they all over me?

15:52.368 --> 15:53.535
That's what I wanted to ask.

16:02.586 --> 16:05.047
I'm sorry
about yesterday's misunderstanding.

16:05.631 --> 16:06.966
I was too harsh.

16:09.093 --> 16:10.177
Well…

16:10.803 --> 16:13.681
I totally get it.

16:14.306 --> 16:15.307
Let's call it even.

16:16.141 --> 16:17.184
The envelope of money!

16:17.267 --> 16:19.770
I put it in the corner of your trailer,
so don't forget it.

16:19.853 --> 16:20.771
I don't need it.

16:21.355 --> 16:22.606
I don't need it either.

16:23.315 --> 16:24.608
You said it was expensive.

16:24.692 --> 16:25.609
Please…

16:26.527 --> 16:27.611
Hey, I'm Dam Ye-jin.

17:16.285 --> 17:17.494
Dam Ye-jin?

17:23.375 --> 17:24.418
Hurry up.

17:31.800 --> 17:34.636
Ma'am, you can just pay later
when you get off.

17:34.720 --> 17:37.347
-It's not that…
-Geez.

17:37.431 --> 17:40.017
Aren't you hungry?
I bet you didn't have any breakfast.

17:40.100 --> 17:41.101
Eat this.

17:41.977 --> 17:43.812
It must be tough.

17:47.149 --> 17:50.319
Sang-geum, why would you give
that grumpy man any food?

18:15.219 --> 18:19.848
WE SPENT OUR TWENTIES TOGETHER

18:33.153 --> 18:34.404
Hey, Ae-ra!

18:41.787 --> 18:43.664
We met when we were eight,

18:44.456 --> 18:45.582
but now we're 40.

18:46.792 --> 18:47.751
Forty!

18:47.835 --> 18:49.419
We're "Young Forty"!

18:50.379 --> 18:51.588
Hey, Ae-ra.

18:51.672 --> 18:53.632
My next NeoTube video
is going to be called

18:53.715 --> 18:56.510
"Introducing Hidden Gems in our Town."

18:56.593 --> 18:59.888
And of course,
we can't be leaving you out.

18:59.972 --> 19:01.890
You were our student president,
valedictorian,

19:01.974 --> 19:03.851
and leader of the kids
in our neighborhood.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.145
Don't you have anything to do?

19:06.228 --> 19:08.605
I'll film a great clip of you
at that macaron place.

19:08.689 --> 19:09.565
What do you say?

19:11.066 --> 19:12.151
Come on. What do you say?

19:13.944 --> 19:15.821
How many subscribers did you say you have?

19:17.114 --> 19:18.365
Seven…

19:18.949 --> 19:20.284
subscribers.

19:22.870 --> 19:23.996
Will you do it if I get ten?

19:24.788 --> 19:25.956
-Are you crazy?
-Fifteen?

19:26.039 --> 19:27.833
-That's enough.
-Twenty?

19:29.042 --> 19:30.961
Born and raised in Deokpung,

19:31.044 --> 19:34.089
I'm Deokpung rep Park Kwang-mo,
and I'm here today to introduce

19:34.173 --> 19:37.134
these plastic bottle pinwheels.

19:37.217 --> 19:39.595
It's a budget-friendly mole repellent.

19:39.678 --> 19:41.054
When the wind blows,

19:41.138 --> 19:44.016
these bottles spin around,
and the vibrations go underground.

19:44.099 --> 19:47.978
The moles think
it's an earthquake and run off.

19:48.061 --> 19:49.646
It's very budget-friendly

19:49.730 --> 19:50.647
and easy to install--

19:50.731 --> 19:51.565
What's that?

19:53.609 --> 19:56.987
Right as I speak,
here comes our village's true gem.

19:57.070 --> 19:58.572
It's Mechoori.

20:00.199 --> 20:01.408
He's coming.

20:02.576 --> 20:04.161
He's still coming.

20:05.662 --> 20:07.414
He should stop coming now.

20:08.332 --> 20:10.042
To all the fans of Park Kwang-mo TV--

20:10.125 --> 20:11.293
Hey!

20:12.085 --> 20:13.378
Hey, Mechoori!

20:18.217 --> 20:21.303
You can't be drowsy driving
around the rice paddies.

20:22.512 --> 20:24.223
I didn't get enough sleep.

20:25.015 --> 20:27.935
Why? Was there a mosquito?

20:28.644 --> 20:31.396
It was something
more persistent than a mosquito.

20:32.022 --> 20:33.023
What?

20:34.399 --> 20:35.400
What are you saying?

20:35.484 --> 20:36.485
Mom?

20:37.736 --> 20:39.613
Mom…

20:41.907 --> 20:42.783
Mom.

20:44.243 --> 20:46.245
Just go and get some rest today.

20:46.745 --> 20:49.289
I'll take care of the farm.

20:49.957 --> 20:52.042
All right. I'd appreciate that.

20:52.125 --> 20:53.043
Sure.

21:04.054 --> 21:05.347
What is that?

21:08.976 --> 21:09.810
What?

21:09.893 --> 21:11.520
Mechoori, what's that?

21:21.446 --> 21:23.532
-Please do it as fast as you can.
-Yes, sir.

21:31.123 --> 21:33.208
Mu-won, come on out.

21:33.292 --> 21:34.293
Hey.

21:36.253 --> 21:37.087
You're home.

21:47.055 --> 21:47.889
Explain this.

21:47.973 --> 21:49.474
Explain what?

21:49.558 --> 21:51.685
Didn't you see?
They're doing construction.

21:51.768 --> 21:52.769
We're building your lab.

21:52.853 --> 21:54.604
Without even asking me? What is this?

21:54.688 --> 21:56.815
You're the one who changed your number.

21:56.898 --> 21:58.608
I was going to tell you in advance.

22:00.027 --> 22:02.112
I wanted to get it done
while you were at the farm.

22:02.195 --> 22:03.613
I told you I won't do it.

22:05.907 --> 22:07.951
Are you just going to farm here forever?

22:08.035 --> 22:10.078
Is this really the life you wanted?

22:10.871 --> 22:12.414
-Yes.
-No.

22:13.248 --> 22:15.334
You're the happiest when you're in a lab.

22:19.504 --> 22:21.048
-We did it!
-We did it!

22:21.673 --> 22:24.259
-We did it!
-We actually did it!

22:24.343 --> 22:25.802
Finally!

22:26.428 --> 22:28.680
Chang-ho made it big in Bangkok.

22:28.764 --> 22:30.891
He said business suits him
way better than research.

22:30.974 --> 22:33.393
But what about you?
How long are you going to live like this?

22:34.019 --> 22:35.812
I told you.

22:35.896 --> 22:37.647
-I like the way things are now.
-Just wait.

22:37.731 --> 22:41.485
That lab is going to produce
a game changer that will rock Korea.

22:41.568 --> 22:42.611
Sir!

22:43.612 --> 22:45.864
Why can't you understand
what I'm saying? Hey!

22:51.953 --> 22:54.456
Sir… Excuse me!

22:54.539 --> 22:55.457
Yes?

22:55.540 --> 22:57.334
Could you stop for a bit?
How about a break?

22:57.417 --> 22:58.335
-Pardon?
-Take a break.

22:58.418 --> 23:00.212
-Sure.
-Thank you.

23:00.295 --> 23:01.421
Let's take a break.

23:04.299 --> 23:05.926
I seriously can't believe you.

23:07.552 --> 23:11.223
Do you know how many calls
I got from L'Étoile today?

23:11.306 --> 23:12.140
They call nonstop--

23:16.144 --> 23:17.145
L'ÉTOILE CHA JOONG-HOON

23:17.229 --> 23:18.730
It's driving me crazy too.

23:21.900 --> 23:24.778
Meet them again and make it clear
that we won't renew the contract.

23:24.861 --> 23:26.279
You tell them.

23:27.072 --> 23:29.783
If you're half as cold to them
as you are to me, they'll give up.

23:29.866 --> 23:30.951
You do it.

23:37.040 --> 23:38.041
What are you… Hey.

23:39.334 --> 23:40.335
Hello?

23:45.465 --> 23:46.466
Why haven't you left yet?

23:46.550 --> 23:48.343
-I'm leaving now.
-Yes, please go.

23:51.763 --> 23:52.848
Gosh, you scared me.

23:54.599 --> 23:55.600
Hey,

23:55.684 --> 23:57.644
you still don't know who I am?

23:59.813 --> 24:01.565
I'm Kang Mu-won.

24:02.274 --> 24:03.525
Kang Mu-won!

24:08.488 --> 24:10.448
I can't let you go looking like this.

24:24.421 --> 24:25.630
All done.

24:54.868 --> 24:58.496
Why didn't you show me
a perfect suit like this?

24:58.580 --> 25:00.749
It's the same suit

25:00.832 --> 25:02.125
you are wearing.

25:02.667 --> 25:03.585
What?

25:24.981 --> 25:26.233
You're killing it.

25:29.736 --> 25:30.612
Stop!

25:30.695 --> 25:32.155
Please, stop!

25:35.200 --> 25:37.160
Yes, could we please stop now?

25:37.827 --> 25:39.204
I told you there's no need.

25:39.287 --> 25:41.456
-Just take it, will you?
-Mu-won.

25:42.123 --> 25:43.583
Can't I just take a taxi?

25:43.667 --> 25:47.170
Listen. All these little details
are needed to gain the upper hand.

25:47.254 --> 25:50.257
No matter how well you fight,
you can't win a war without weapons…

25:50.340 --> 25:51.341
I'm going to be late.

25:51.424 --> 25:53.009
Hey, wear this instead.

25:53.093 --> 25:54.052
Mu-won.

25:55.387 --> 25:57.764
All right, fine. Then, just take the car.

26:12.028 --> 26:13.196
Nice to meet you.

26:13.280 --> 26:15.865
I'm Gojeuneok Bio's co-CEO, Lee Hae-seok.

26:15.949 --> 26:18.493
Nice to meet you.
I'm Eric Seo from L'Étoile.

26:21.621 --> 26:22.706
I admit that last time,

26:22.789 --> 26:24.958
our order quantity
of raw materials was unreasonable.

26:25.041 --> 26:27.752
This is a revised contract
with the condition

26:27.836 --> 26:30.380
that the raw material supply
will increase gradually.

26:30.463 --> 26:32.007
To increase raw material production,

26:32.090 --> 26:33.758
it also says we will be covering

26:34.259 --> 26:36.052
facility expansion costs and labor costs.

26:36.136 --> 26:39.931
It seems you still don't
fully understand why we won't re-sign.

26:40.015 --> 26:42.350
Gojeuneok's first rule

26:42.434 --> 26:44.853
is for me to have full control
over the entire process.

26:45.520 --> 26:48.273
We cannot continue with a company
that breaks this rule.

26:48.356 --> 26:51.192
With proper facilities and personnel,
I'm sure it will be manageable.

26:51.276 --> 26:54.321
Those things alone can't guarantee
the quality of the materials.

26:54.404 --> 26:56.156
Don't you want more people

26:56.656 --> 26:58.158
to use better quality essence?

26:58.908 --> 27:00.368
That intention may become a mistake.

27:00.452 --> 27:01.619
No, it will become hope.

27:05.040 --> 27:08.251
Hope can help us get started,

27:08.335 --> 27:10.420
but it can't take responsibility
for the outcome.

27:11.588 --> 27:13.381
That reckless optimism

27:14.132 --> 27:15.842
is exactly why we can't work together.

27:15.925 --> 27:19.637
Then, what if we take the same quantity
as our previous contract?

27:19.721 --> 27:21.431
I heard you're preparing to launch on HIT.

27:21.514 --> 27:23.058
We're only selling a limited amount.

27:23.141 --> 27:26.186
I'm sure they'll request
a bigger quantity for the next broadcast.

27:26.269 --> 27:29.356
There's no reason to continue working
with a company that backtracks…

27:32.901 --> 27:34.027
on prior agreements.

27:39.366 --> 27:41.493
I believe I've made myself clear,

27:41.576 --> 27:42.869
so I'll head out.

27:44.996 --> 27:46.581
You sure you won't regret it?

27:47.791 --> 27:49.000
This is L'Étoile.

27:58.843 --> 28:00.762
Maybe I shouldn't have said
that last line.

28:06.810 --> 28:08.770
What did you need to tell me so urgently?

28:08.853 --> 28:10.105
I had something to share.

28:10.188 --> 28:12.941
Gojeuneok Bio has co-CEOs.

28:13.024 --> 28:16.403
Kang Mu-won and Lee Hae-seok.

28:17.821 --> 28:18.905
Lee Hae-seok?

28:18.988 --> 28:21.491
Lee Hae-seok has control
over deciding the contract renewal,

28:22.075 --> 28:23.576
but he's quite firm in his stance.

28:23.660 --> 28:24.619
You met him?

28:24.702 --> 28:26.079
Where is he right now?

28:26.955 --> 28:29.040
He's not someone who's that easy to meet.

28:29.124 --> 28:30.542
Him too?

28:30.625 --> 28:32.502
It's the same with the farm owner.

28:32.585 --> 28:34.629
I failed to meet him so many times.

28:35.171 --> 28:36.339
It seems

28:36.423 --> 28:39.467
people who are very similar to each other
work at Gojeuneok Bio.

28:43.346 --> 28:44.723
Let's go with Plan B now.

28:44.806 --> 28:47.225
If there are two of them,
we need to match their numbers.

28:47.308 --> 28:49.894
I'll try and convince
Mr. Lee Hae-seok from now on.

28:53.606 --> 28:54.607
Mr. Seo?

28:57.944 --> 29:00.697
You really don't recognize me?

29:02.615 --> 29:04.617
You really don't remember me?

29:08.163 --> 29:09.289
I do.

29:10.790 --> 29:12.417
You remember me?

29:13.793 --> 29:15.295
But why did you pretend not to?

29:16.254 --> 29:17.255
Because I felt so sorry.

29:17.922 --> 29:19.716
I felt bad I couldn't be there that day.

29:21.634 --> 29:22.802
You mean

29:22.886 --> 29:25.430
you wanted to come
but you couldn't, right?

29:25.513 --> 29:26.806
Did something happen that day?

29:28.933 --> 29:30.101
Well, it was a long time ago.

29:31.811 --> 29:35.273
Then, how about we chat like back then
until you can remember?

29:36.649 --> 29:37.817
Mr. Seo.

29:39.652 --> 29:42.155
All right. Let's focus on Plan B.

29:46.326 --> 29:49.621
Can't we just find
a different raw material producer?

29:49.704 --> 29:52.290
I talked to headquarters about that too.

29:52.373 --> 29:55.543
But apparently, they tried to farm
white flower noori mushrooms in France

29:55.627 --> 29:56.753
and failed.

29:56.836 --> 29:58.797
And even if they had succeeded,

29:58.880 --> 30:00.799
the process of extracting the ingredients

30:00.882 --> 30:02.592
is Gojeuneok's exclusive technology.

30:02.675 --> 30:05.386
Then, the conclusion is
that they're the only choice.

30:05.470 --> 30:07.180
What did the farm owner say?

30:07.263 --> 30:09.516
Don't get me started.
I didn't even get to meet him.

30:09.599 --> 30:13.353
The workers on the farm there
say he's really strict.

30:13.436 --> 30:15.647
And he seems to hate
communicating with outsiders.

30:17.982 --> 30:19.400
These two people…

30:19.484 --> 30:21.110
They're virtually doppelgängers.

30:21.194 --> 30:22.445
STRICT, DIFFICULT TO REACH

30:23.196 --> 30:24.614
Maybe the same guy?

30:25.448 --> 30:26.282
Mr. Hwang!

30:26.366 --> 30:29.202
-Right?
-What do we do with him?

30:29.285 --> 30:30.370
-That was his best?
-No way.

30:30.453 --> 30:31.454
-That was lame.
-Fire him.

30:32.497 --> 30:34.374
I mean, we can't say it's impossible…

30:35.625 --> 30:36.459
Look.

30:36.543 --> 30:39.462
How can someone manage
the company and the farm at the same time?

30:39.546 --> 30:41.506
Do you think he can just teleport
back and forth?

30:42.465 --> 30:45.468
It's tough to even manage one job,
you know.

30:45.552 --> 30:47.178
I'm having such a hard time right now.

30:53.101 --> 30:55.311
ANYOUNG RICE

30:58.648 --> 30:59.858
Yes.

30:59.941 --> 31:02.402
Anyway, please call me
if there's anything available.

31:02.485 --> 31:06.906
Come on. Weekends don't matter.
I need the money.

31:07.740 --> 31:09.909
Yes. All right, bye.

31:37.312 --> 31:38.521
Use this for baby formula.

31:45.486 --> 31:46.446
Honey?

31:46.529 --> 31:47.864
Hey, it's me.

31:47.947 --> 31:50.199
-Why aren't you coming inside?
-It's nothing. Go on in.

31:50.283 --> 31:52.952
Hey, did you order rice?

31:53.036 --> 31:55.038
Hey, Se-jung. How was your day?

31:55.121 --> 31:58.833
PROUD AND CONFIDENT, DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

32:26.402 --> 32:28.279
I'm sorry for everything.

32:30.782 --> 32:32.158
I…

32:33.159 --> 32:37.956
I was struggling to get by,
and it made me struggle to be generous.

32:38.790 --> 32:43.336
I thought I was all alone in this world
and did a lot of things I was ashamed of.

32:46.047 --> 32:48.883
From now on, I'll stick
to the precise schedule

32:49.801 --> 32:51.094
and I won't speed.

32:52.136 --> 32:57.100
You can tell me whenever you need
to use the restroom before we leave.

32:58.393 --> 32:59.560
Thank you so much!

33:02.605 --> 33:04.732
-Thank you!
-Thank you!

33:23.418 --> 33:25.628
Just think of this
as saving someone's life.

33:25.712 --> 33:27.380
Please help me out just this once.

33:28.214 --> 33:32.635
Ma'am, I'm telling you
I'm really busy right now.

33:32.719 --> 33:34.971
We get the most views
when you appear on our channel!

33:38.266 --> 33:40.518
Hello, HIT subscribers!

33:40.601 --> 33:42.437
I'm home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

33:42.520 --> 33:46.232
Today, I'll be trying out a day
as a call center agent

33:46.315 --> 33:49.777
to personally hear
the kind of difficulties

33:49.861 --> 33:52.321
our customers actually may have.

33:52.405 --> 33:53.865
All right, shall we go?

33:54.949 --> 33:56.534
Hello, this is--

33:56.617 --> 33:58.369
That shampoo you're selling now…

33:58.453 --> 34:01.664
I only want to buy half of Set 1,
so give me a 50% discount.

34:01.748 --> 34:03.958
Ma'am, I'm really sorry,

34:04.042 --> 34:07.170
but I'm not authorized
to adjust the set or the price.

34:07.920 --> 34:10.381
Wait, you want me to buy something
I can't even use all of?

34:10.465 --> 34:12.216
Are you encouraging
unnecessary consumption?

34:13.259 --> 34:15.470
Hello, how may I help you?

34:15.553 --> 34:17.722
Well, I want to return
the short rib soup I bought.

34:17.805 --> 34:20.391
Was there anything wrong
with the soup you ordered?

34:20.475 --> 34:22.560
I ate it, but it wasn't to my taste.

34:22.643 --> 34:25.021
So you sampled one pack,
but it wasn't to your--

34:25.104 --> 34:26.397
No.

34:26.481 --> 34:28.775
I ate all of them,

34:28.858 --> 34:31.152
but they didn't taste good,
and the bones were too big.

34:31.235 --> 34:32.570
They were so heavy.

34:32.653 --> 34:34.447
You ate everything,
so how can you return--

34:34.530 --> 34:37.867
I said I ate everything!
I didn't leave any!

34:37.950 --> 34:39.494
-Hello--
-You better fix this.

34:39.577 --> 34:40.453
Pardon?

34:44.415 --> 34:46.250
How may I help you, sir?

34:46.334 --> 34:49.504
My family has fallen apart
because of these damn golf shoes.

34:49.587 --> 34:52.965
You ordered
white women's golf shoes in size 235.

34:53.049 --> 34:56.010
Why would you send them
the next morning after my order?

34:56.094 --> 34:57.720
My wife saw these!

34:57.804 --> 34:58.888
-Pardon?
-Forget it.

34:58.971 --> 35:00.598
My wife's filing for divorce,

35:00.681 --> 35:03.601
and I'm going to be bleeding money
with alimony and everything,

35:03.684 --> 35:05.770
so you better compensate me
for emotional distress.

35:05.853 --> 35:07.063
Is he out of his damn…

35:09.232 --> 35:10.733
I can't believe these people.

35:10.817 --> 35:12.985
Excuse me, Ms. Dam?

35:13.694 --> 35:17.156
Could you please just take
one call smoothly?

35:19.242 --> 35:20.284
Sorry.

35:22.954 --> 35:24.664
I'll do a proper call this time.

35:24.747 --> 35:26.082
I will now be a yes-man.

35:26.165 --> 35:27.708
-Yes-man.
-Yes-man.

35:27.792 --> 35:28.751
That's right.

35:28.835 --> 35:30.044
Yes! Yes!

35:30.128 --> 35:32.380
And there's a call right on time.
Let's get into it.

35:32.463 --> 35:34.590
Hello, this is Dam Ye-jin,
your agent for today--

35:34.674 --> 35:35.967
-Is this HIT?
-Yes, it is.

35:36.050 --> 35:37.885
How can you sell
a ridiculous item like this?

35:40.721 --> 35:42.974
Is there something wrong
with the item you purchased?

35:43.057 --> 35:45.309
Don't you have a quality control team?

35:45.852 --> 35:48.729
You shipped out something
that doesn't even work properly.

35:48.813 --> 35:50.481
This is how you handle things?

35:50.565 --> 35:52.567
You're using that
as a drying rack for laundry?

35:52.650 --> 35:56.487
No matter how long I sit in there,
I don't sweat at all.

35:56.571 --> 35:57.530
Is it broken?

35:57.613 --> 35:59.323
This was so expensive.

35:59.407 --> 36:02.243
Gosh, it's giving me a headache.

36:04.120 --> 36:07.206
Whatever's wrong with it,
it's just an expensive wooden chair now.

36:07.290 --> 36:08.207
I see.

36:08.291 --> 36:10.960
You trusted home shopping host
Dam Ye-jin and bought it,

36:11.043 --> 36:13.629
-but there was an issue--
-I've never trusted Dam Ye-jin.

36:13.713 --> 36:14.881
I'm very disappointed though.

36:14.964 --> 36:16.799
I see.

36:16.883 --> 36:17.842
Please wait one moment.

36:24.015 --> 36:25.808
Excuse me, sir,

36:26.309 --> 36:29.770
but could you tell me your name
so I can check your purchase information?

36:32.148 --> 36:33.065
It's Lee Hae-seok.

36:33.149 --> 36:34.066
DEOKPUNG VILLAGE

36:34.150 --> 36:35.651
It's Lee Hae-seok.

36:36.402 --> 36:37.987
Gojeuneok Bio has co-CEOs.

36:38.070 --> 36:40.865
Kang Mu-won and Lee Hae-seok.

36:41.449 --> 36:42.283
These two people…

36:42.366 --> 36:44.452
They're virtually doppelgängers.
Maybe the same guy?

36:44.535 --> 36:45.578
Him too?

36:45.661 --> 36:47.079
It's the same with the farm owner.

36:47.163 --> 36:48.789
I failed to meet him so many times.

36:48.873 --> 36:50.666
Mr. "Lee something Seok"? Mr. Lee!

36:50.750 --> 36:52.793
For privacy reasons,
the middle character is hidden.

36:52.877 --> 36:54.712
-What's your full name?
-It's Matthew.

36:55.630 --> 36:57.089
Gojeuneok Bio has co-CEOs.

36:57.173 --> 36:58.674
The farm owner… "Lee something Seok"…

36:58.758 --> 36:59.717
It's Lee Hae-seok.

37:01.344 --> 37:02.261
FARM OWNER

37:08.184 --> 37:09.936
LEE HAE-SEOK

37:10.686 --> 37:12.980
It's Lee Hae-seok.

37:17.443 --> 37:19.278
Sir, can you wait just one moment?

37:20.821 --> 37:23.783
Tell him the staff in charge
will come in person to take care of it.

37:29.413 --> 37:32.208
Seriously, thank you so much.

37:32.291 --> 37:33.334
Thank you!

37:43.678 --> 37:46.430
Hit or push through my car if you want.

37:46.514 --> 37:47.598
No!

37:47.682 --> 37:51.644
I've had men follow me in their sports
cars before, but a tractor is a first.

37:51.727 --> 37:53.104
It's pretty unique.

37:53.187 --> 37:55.815
I guess "Mechoori" means Matthew Lee,

37:55.898 --> 37:57.566
not "mechoori" as in quail.

38:00.236 --> 38:02.780
That jerk.

38:05.574 --> 38:07.827
Ye-jin! You must've lost your mind!

38:07.910 --> 38:08.869
I must've been crazy!

38:09.453 --> 38:10.955
Wait. I can make it up to him.

38:11.038 --> 38:12.123
Can I?

38:12.206 --> 38:13.040
I can.

38:14.458 --> 38:16.127
I don't think I can.

38:16.210 --> 38:18.129
No, I have to.

38:18.212 --> 38:19.630
I have to.

38:19.714 --> 38:20.840
I must.

38:20.923 --> 38:22.258
I can do it.

38:22.341 --> 38:23.175
Right.

38:23.259 --> 38:24.385
Let's give it a try.

38:56.375 --> 38:58.544
Hello!

38:58.627 --> 39:00.671
It's nice to see you again.

39:07.887 --> 39:09.096
Did you forget the agreement?

39:09.180 --> 39:10.681
I'm here today because you called me.

39:10.765 --> 39:12.058
I'm your call center agent.

39:15.394 --> 39:17.646
Just give me the number
for the staff in charge.

39:23.569 --> 39:24.445
HIT
DAM YE-JIN

39:26.572 --> 39:28.157
-Are you kidding me?
-What?

39:28.240 --> 39:30.868
I sold the products,
so I'm the staff in charge.

39:32.286 --> 39:34.330
Where's your bathtub, sir?

39:35.873 --> 39:37.333
Fine. Go take a look,

39:38.626 --> 39:39.752
Ms. Dam.

39:40.586 --> 39:43.130
Yes, sir! I'll make my way in!

39:59.146 --> 40:01.065
I ran a detailed inspection,

40:01.148 --> 40:02.775
and it's not broken.

40:02.858 --> 40:05.069
It was just operator error, sir.

40:05.152 --> 40:06.737
This blanket

40:06.821 --> 40:08.864
will be included for preheating.

40:08.948 --> 40:13.327
Cover the top with this blanket,
turn the power on, and wait 20 minutes.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.745
Please keep this in mind.

40:14.829 --> 40:15.955
I explained

40:16.038 --> 40:19.417
that you have to cover it
with this blanket to preheat it.

40:19.500 --> 40:23.003
I emphasized it several times,
but I guess you didn't listen.

40:24.839 --> 40:26.257
You can't just insist it's working.

40:26.340 --> 40:27.425
"Insist"?

40:28.050 --> 40:29.593
Then, did you think

40:29.677 --> 40:32.471
we sent this blanket
as a meaningless freebie?

40:33.389 --> 40:37.560
Are you embarrassed because you complained
that a perfectly fine machine was broken?

40:38.185 --> 40:39.395
Seriously?

40:40.020 --> 40:41.480
It doesn't make you sweat!

40:44.442 --> 40:45.901
There's no need to explain.

40:45.985 --> 40:48.320
I'll just show you
whether you sweat or not.

40:49.405 --> 40:50.698
Open that too.

40:51.449 --> 40:53.826
Don't file another complaint later
saying that's broken too.

40:55.244 --> 40:57.538
Fine. We'll open that too.

40:59.039 --> 41:01.584
It's already hot and steamy
with the preheating, isn't it?

41:02.710 --> 41:04.920
It's not nearly hot enough to sweat.

41:05.671 --> 41:06.505
You better hope so.

41:10.885 --> 41:12.136
Hold on a minute.

41:12.720 --> 41:13.846
What are you doing?

41:13.929 --> 41:15.431
What?

41:15.514 --> 41:18.267
You're pressing pressure points
that help you sweat.

41:18.976 --> 41:20.561
You think those tricks will fool me?

41:21.479 --> 41:24.148
If massaging your temples caused sweat,
all saunas would disappear.

41:24.231 --> 41:27.401
I work on little sleep and suffer
from headaches due to such bias.

41:34.116 --> 41:35.534
You're sweating!

41:35.618 --> 41:38.329
See? You're sweating! Right there!

41:42.625 --> 41:43.709
The ceiling's leaking.

41:43.792 --> 41:46.045
The ceiling? Why?
It looks completely fine.

41:46.128 --> 41:47.463
Mr. Mechoori, look here.

41:47.546 --> 41:48.881
Look here, not the ceiling.

41:48.964 --> 41:51.008
Mr. Mechoori!

41:51.091 --> 41:52.593
You see all this sweat forming here?

41:53.385 --> 41:54.470
My house is usually hot.

41:57.223 --> 41:58.224
Raise your arms.

41:59.016 --> 42:00.726
-What?
-Raise your arms.

42:01.435 --> 42:02.269
Why?

42:04.438 --> 42:05.731
What?

42:05.814 --> 42:07.900
-Mr. Mechoori, let me see your arms.
-Why?

42:07.983 --> 42:09.401
Come on. I need to check something.

42:09.485 --> 42:11.445
-Check what?
-Just raise them once.

42:11.529 --> 42:12.655
-For what?
-Just one minute.

42:12.738 --> 42:14.198
-Go away.
-It's over for you.

42:14.281 --> 42:16.867
-I got you. Raise your arms.
-Hey, what are you…

42:16.951 --> 42:17.910
Sit. Raise your arms.

42:18.494 --> 42:19.745
Ms. Dam!

42:19.828 --> 42:21.038
Tickle, tickle!

42:21.121 --> 42:21.956
Ms. Dam!

42:22.039 --> 42:23.123
-What?
-Wait…

42:23.999 --> 42:24.875
Okay, fine!

42:24.959 --> 42:26.835
-I take back my complaint!
-No, it's too late.

42:26.919 --> 42:28.420
-I need to see--
-Ms. Dam!

42:46.939 --> 42:49.358
TEMPERATURE

42:49.441 --> 42:51.193
ERROR

43:01.036 --> 43:02.913
I guess you were a bit embarrassed,

43:02.997 --> 43:04.623
seeing how you even gave me tea.

43:05.833 --> 43:08.669
If you're not going to drink it, then go.
Our business is over.

43:09.628 --> 43:12.464
How long are you going to
keep playing dumb for?

43:13.132 --> 43:16.176
You think I came all the way here
just to check on the product?

43:16.260 --> 43:17.845
Don't look down on HIT's QC team.

43:17.928 --> 43:19.513
You're the one who overreacted.

43:20.139 --> 43:21.932
I simply made a call
to the service center.

43:22.891 --> 43:23.976
That's what I mean.

43:25.019 --> 43:27.938
Don't you get why I overreacted?

43:30.816 --> 43:32.484
Let me formally introduce myself,

43:32.568 --> 43:34.486
Mr. Lee Hae-seok.

43:39.575 --> 43:42.745
I'll see you again, Mr. Lee!

43:51.211 --> 43:52.338
Changsik.

43:53.047 --> 43:54.340
Changsik!

43:54.423 --> 43:55.799
Hey, Changsik.

43:57.843 --> 43:59.887
Are you ignoring me too?

44:01.847 --> 44:02.890
Give me your paw.

44:03.682 --> 44:06.185
Hey, I'm feeling really down today.
Come on.

44:07.353 --> 44:08.896
Just once, Changsik.

44:08.979 --> 44:09.813
Give me your paw!

44:11.607 --> 44:14.401
Hey, come on. Give me your paw.

44:14.485 --> 44:15.736
Hey.

44:15.819 --> 44:18.364
-Ma'am.
-Give this to him.

44:21.367 --> 44:23.410
Hey, whether it's a dog or a human,

44:23.494 --> 44:26.705
they say you should feed them
before telling them what to do.

44:26.789 --> 44:30.042
If you want him to listen to you,
you need to feed him first.

44:31.627 --> 44:32.670
Right.

44:33.587 --> 44:35.214
I need to feed him first.

44:36.674 --> 44:37.675
Changsik, here.

44:42.638 --> 44:44.682
What would he like then?

44:46.600 --> 44:48.894
That's right! Your bathtub, ma'am.

44:49.770 --> 44:52.564
I got a call from Mechoori.
He said it's fine.

44:53.649 --> 44:55.401
You came all the way here for nothing.

44:55.484 --> 44:58.862
It's fine. I came for other reasons too.
And I was missing your potatoes.

45:00.280 --> 45:02.032
You want some potatoes before you go?

45:02.116 --> 45:05.202
Ma'am, if you keep asking me
to stay overnight like this…

45:05.828 --> 45:07.079
Sure!

45:10.624 --> 45:11.625
FARMING LOG

46:47.262 --> 46:48.514
Are you up?

46:49.097 --> 46:51.808
Yes. Are you going somewhere?

46:51.892 --> 46:55.020
I'm going to the mushroom farm.
They're short-handed.

46:57.064 --> 46:58.649
-Where?
-The mushroom farm.

47:34.434 --> 47:35.352
Did you sleep well?

47:36.311 --> 47:37.437
The weather's so nice.

47:37.521 --> 47:38.605
-Good morning.
-Hi.

47:39.189 --> 47:40.816
-Hello.
-Hi.

47:41.942 --> 47:42.859
-Good morning.
-Hey.

47:42.943 --> 47:44.528
-Good morning. Did you sleep well?
-Yes.

47:55.789 --> 47:56.832
Ms. Dam?

47:57.916 --> 47:59.042
How did you know?

48:01.044 --> 48:02.087
Well,

48:02.754 --> 48:04.381
I guess farming clothes

48:04.464 --> 48:05.966
can't hide my beauty.

48:08.260 --> 48:09.511
Right…

48:10.345 --> 48:11.888
This is my last warning.

48:11.972 --> 48:13.432
Please, just leave.

48:14.182 --> 48:16.018
Sweetie, come here!

48:16.101 --> 48:17.561
Yes, ma'am!

48:17.644 --> 48:18.854
She's calling me.

48:18.937 --> 48:19.896
Wait…

48:20.814 --> 48:22.274
I'm coming!

48:28.447 --> 48:35.245
Deokpung's pride and treasure,
the white flower noori mushrooms!

48:35.871 --> 48:41.793
As always,
please handle each one with care!

48:41.877 --> 48:43.045
Come on!

48:43.128 --> 48:44.171
Let's go!

48:44.254 --> 48:46.423
-Let's go!
-Let's go!

49:04.608 --> 49:06.443
We're getting off work right on the dot.

49:06.526 --> 49:07.986
-That's right!
-On the dot!

49:08.070 --> 49:10.530
Our work is not over yet!

49:10.614 --> 49:11.490
Deokpung's--

49:11.573 --> 49:12.991
Let's go!

49:13.075 --> 49:14.660
Make sure to wrap up for us!

49:16.453 --> 49:17.829
See you!

49:26.755 --> 49:27.589
Good work today.

49:28.715 --> 49:29.549
Right.

49:34.221 --> 49:37.724
I'm going through all this effort,
so could you please spare me some time?

49:37.808 --> 49:39.601
Did you review the materials I left you?

49:40.769 --> 49:41.603
No.

49:42.312 --> 49:44.690
Then, just give me ten… No, five minutes.

49:44.773 --> 49:46.525
Give me five minutes, and I'll brief you.

49:46.608 --> 49:47.442
It's fine.

49:47.526 --> 49:50.821
Can't you reconsider
and renew the contract?

49:50.904 --> 49:53.699
L'Étoile said they'll just accept
the quantity you can produce,

49:53.782 --> 49:55.867
so there's no issue now.

49:55.951 --> 49:57.786
They already broke our trust.

49:57.869 --> 50:01.164
We can't work with people
who have already broken their promise.

50:01.248 --> 50:02.624
Are you a robot or something?

50:02.708 --> 50:04.376
Business is done by people.

50:04.459 --> 50:06.211
It can't be perfect all the time.

50:06.294 --> 50:07.713
Ms. Dam.

50:09.089 --> 50:11.591
Can you put spilled milk
back in the glass?

50:12.342 --> 50:15.220
Look, I'm saying
we can quickly wipe it with a towel.

50:15.303 --> 50:16.471
And if we dry it in the sun

50:17.139 --> 50:18.807
and squeeze it out, we can reuse it.

50:18.890 --> 50:21.017
If it's not dried properly,
it'll get moldy.

50:21.101 --> 50:23.603
That's what we call contamination.
All right?

50:29.151 --> 50:30.944
I understand what you're saying,

50:31.027 --> 50:32.946
but if you could just reconsider…

50:33.029 --> 50:35.824
I'm practically pleading, sir. Please?

50:35.907 --> 50:38.368
If we discuss this further,
you might change your mind…

50:38.452 --> 50:40.203
My hand!

50:40.287 --> 50:42.581
My hand was almost caught in the gate.

50:45.917 --> 50:47.878
If you take one step inside,

50:47.961 --> 50:49.588
I'll immediately call the police.

50:54.968 --> 50:56.094
Ms. Dam!

50:56.178 --> 50:59.556
Hey, we even did a sauna session together.
You're so mean.

50:59.639 --> 51:00.974
Will you please leave?

51:01.850 --> 51:02.934
I will but…

51:03.560 --> 51:04.519
What are you doing?

51:04.603 --> 51:06.563
-I'll leave, but if we could talk…
-Hey…

51:06.646 --> 51:09.232
-You're using force?
-You're the one pushing right now.

51:09.316 --> 51:11.026
Just a moment. Please, sir.

51:11.109 --> 51:12.611
-Ms. Dam!
-Mr. Lee.

51:13.153 --> 51:14.780
Mr. Lee!

51:22.370 --> 51:23.205
"IN"

51:23.288 --> 51:24.247
CHARACTER FOR "PERSON"

51:24.331 --> 51:25.957
DERIVED FROM PEOPLE
LEANING ON EACH OTHER

51:31.004 --> 51:32.172
Please get off me.

51:35.717 --> 51:36.843
No, don't come in. Get out.

51:36.927 --> 51:38.929
I'm going to!

51:40.430 --> 51:41.640
For crying out loud.

51:58.031 --> 51:58.865
Ms. Dam?

52:03.078 --> 52:04.079
Hang on…

52:10.877 --> 52:13.547
I do understand your decision, Mr. Lee.

52:13.630 --> 52:15.215
But that makes me want this more.

52:15.298 --> 52:16.967
I really want to introduce an essence

52:17.050 --> 52:19.219
made with good ingredients
to our customers.

52:21.054 --> 52:23.348
Gosh, talking all by myself
is making my mouth hurt.

52:23.431 --> 52:24.558
Oh, dear.

52:27.018 --> 52:28.395
Give it a rest.

52:28.478 --> 52:30.313
It really hurts.
What if it's broken forever?

52:32.524 --> 52:33.692
It's hurting so much.

52:35.485 --> 52:37.696
Okay, it's all done.

52:37.779 --> 52:40.949
It's not good if it gets wet,
so be careful.

52:41.032 --> 52:44.953
Is it okay to take this off
just for a moment this evening?

52:45.453 --> 52:46.288
Sorry?

52:47.289 --> 52:50.041
WOORI DEOKPUNG MEDICAL CLINIC

52:54.546 --> 52:56.840
Why did you have to fall
so dramatically like that?

52:56.923 --> 52:58.884
Were you trying
to blackmail me with an injury?

53:00.635 --> 53:04.598
If I was going to use such tacky methods,
I would've used my beauty first.

53:04.681 --> 53:05.849
So,

53:06.391 --> 53:08.018
should I change my tactics then?

53:13.481 --> 53:15.650
I have a live broadcast at 11:00 p.m.

53:16.401 --> 53:19.779
I can't let my injury stand out
more than the product.

53:20.780 --> 53:23.074
I've prepared so hard for that item too.

53:28.914 --> 53:29.998
It's this way.

53:45.972 --> 53:47.557
I have a live broadcast at 11:00 p.m.

53:47.641 --> 53:51.353
I can't let my injury stand out
more than the product.

54:03.573 --> 54:05.408
HIT

54:05.492 --> 54:07.744
If you look here,
you can adjust the resistance.

54:07.827 --> 54:09.371
Whether beginner or expert,

54:09.454 --> 54:12.374
you can tailor your workout
to match your fitness level.

54:12.457 --> 54:13.875
After you adjust it,

54:13.959 --> 54:18.588
grab the bar,
pull it all the way back, and that's it.

54:18.672 --> 54:21.424
You'll get both cardio
and strength training in one go.

54:21.508 --> 54:23.426
Then, push all the way out with your legs.

54:23.510 --> 54:29.891
You have to pull the bar all the way back
toward your upper abdomen

54:29.975 --> 54:32.143
to maximize your workout.

54:32.227 --> 54:33.353
That must hurt…

54:33.436 --> 54:36.648
It really feels like
you're rowing on water.

54:37.232 --> 54:40.610
There's strong resistance when you pull.

54:44.698 --> 54:45.865
That makes me want this more.

54:45.949 --> 54:47.617
I really want to introduce an essence

54:47.701 --> 54:49.828
made with good ingredients
to our customers.

54:59.504 --> 55:01.131
HIT HOMESHOPPING
DAM YE-JIN

55:14.394 --> 55:15.478
Jin-yi.

55:16.229 --> 55:17.814
What are you doing here at this hour--

55:19.649 --> 55:21.651
You're such a negligent landlord.

55:22.402 --> 55:24.863
Your tenant wasn't paying rent,
but you didn't press them.

55:26.281 --> 55:27.323
I said you didn't have to.

55:27.407 --> 55:29.325
And I told you hundreds of times

55:30.076 --> 55:31.786
I refuse to be treated
like a charity case.

55:35.957 --> 55:36.875
What about Som-yi?

55:36.958 --> 55:39.335
She's busy bragging about the gift
that someone left her.

55:42.380 --> 55:43.381
What was she doing here?

55:50.221 --> 55:51.222
It's nothing.

55:53.308 --> 55:54.309
Nothing?

55:59.314 --> 56:00.356
Hey.

56:02.984 --> 56:04.360
What is it this time?

56:04.444 --> 56:07.614
The Beauty Song essence that Ms. Song's
been preparing for three years…

56:07.697 --> 56:08.531
It's launching soon.

56:09.324 --> 56:10.950
Customers won't buy essence again

56:11.034 --> 56:12.660
a week after buying L'Étoile's essence.

56:12.744 --> 56:14.704
They will if it's good.

56:15.371 --> 56:17.415
You should be focusing
on the product's quality.

56:18.875 --> 56:22.420
Are you really that bent
on dragging Ms. Song down?

56:27.300 --> 56:28.301
Poor Ms. Song.

56:29.594 --> 56:31.971
You really are cruel. Geez.

56:38.103 --> 56:40.146
HIT HOMESHOPPING
DAM YE-JIN

56:55.495 --> 56:58.706
Mu-won, let's end things
with L'Étoile for good.

57:01.000 --> 57:03.253
Send me the list of other clients.

57:14.848 --> 57:18.059
PERILLA LEAVES, BELLFLOWER ROOT,
MEAT PATTIES, STUFFED CUCUMBER KIMCHI

57:19.894 --> 57:22.105
YOU MUST BE BUSY

57:35.785 --> 57:36.953
Welcome back.

57:37.537 --> 57:38.538
Did you eat dinner yet?

57:40.248 --> 57:41.416
I don't have an appetite.

57:44.502 --> 57:45.628
You haven't eaten, have you?

57:45.712 --> 57:48.423
-Come here, I'll make you--
-Please, just…

57:48.506 --> 57:49.883
What's wrong? Are you hurt?

57:51.926 --> 57:53.136
It's nothing.

57:54.304 --> 57:55.138
What about dinner?

57:55.221 --> 57:56.431
Geez.

57:56.514 --> 57:58.725
Can't you stop nagging me about my meals?

57:59.434 --> 58:01.186
I told you a million times I can't eat.

58:01.269 --> 58:03.188
I don't have the time!

58:03.271 --> 58:05.857
Why do you keep giving me food
that I'll end up throwing away?

58:05.940 --> 58:07.358
It just makes me feel bad.

58:11.196 --> 58:13.239
It's okay if you throw them all away.

58:13.323 --> 58:16.493
I just don't want your fridge to be empty

58:16.576 --> 58:18.286
when you want to eat something.

58:19.329 --> 58:20.330
Geez…

58:22.248 --> 58:24.584
You shouldn't just barge in here, Dad.

58:25.210 --> 58:26.419
I'm not a kid.

58:27.253 --> 58:30.590
I told you,
I don't need stuff like this right now!

58:34.052 --> 58:35.428
Why do you always…

58:37.222 --> 58:38.932
just do as you please?

58:45.188 --> 58:46.231
Ye-jin.

58:47.273 --> 58:49.400
Please, don't do this.

58:50.151 --> 58:51.152
But it's true.

58:52.028 --> 58:53.655
Mom abandoned me.

58:54.864 --> 58:57.075
-Ye-jin.
-I don't care anymore.

58:57.742 --> 58:59.327
I'm going to tell everyone.

58:59.410 --> 59:01.496
I'm going to tell them
Song Myeong-hwa's my mom

59:01.579 --> 59:03.248
and that she's a liar.

59:04.916 --> 59:06.876
I told her not to contact you!

59:11.005 --> 59:12.131
What?

59:13.591 --> 59:16.928
Your mom actually did call.

59:17.887 --> 59:19.597
She said she was so startled then,

59:19.681 --> 59:21.933
and she wanted to apologize to you.

59:22.016 --> 59:22.850
But,

59:23.768 --> 59:24.686
I can't…

59:26.437 --> 59:29.566
see you get hurt like that again.

59:30.358 --> 59:33.278
So I told her not to contact you again.

59:33.361 --> 59:34.988
I'm the one who stopped her.

59:35.071 --> 59:35.905
Why?

59:37.198 --> 59:38.449
Why did you do that?

59:40.118 --> 59:41.202
What about me?

59:42.620 --> 59:45.498
Why decide that on your own?
Who are you to stop her?

59:48.459 --> 59:49.460
I'm sorry.

59:54.465 --> 59:55.550
I'm really sorry.

01:00:11.149 --> 01:00:12.150
Sorry.

01:00:15.236 --> 01:00:16.529
I'm really sorry.

01:01:10.458 --> 01:01:14.295
GOJEUNEOK BIO

01:01:33.356 --> 01:01:34.649
Hello?

01:01:34.732 --> 01:01:36.234
Mom.

01:01:38.736 --> 01:01:39.862
Excuse me.

01:01:39.946 --> 01:01:42.073
-I clearly told you--
-It's me, Ye-jin.

01:01:45.159 --> 01:01:46.160
What?

01:01:47.954 --> 01:01:49.205
Who did you say you were?

01:01:49.747 --> 01:01:50.998
Did you see my show?

01:01:52.917 --> 01:01:56.462
Actually, I got hurt today.

01:02:02.552 --> 01:02:04.971
3 MISSED CALLS

01:02:09.016 --> 01:02:10.852
Whenever I moved,

01:02:12.186 --> 01:02:13.730
it hurt so much,

01:02:15.606 --> 01:02:17.775
so I just didn't care…

01:02:19.444 --> 01:02:21.738
and wanted to quit the show.

01:02:24.198 --> 01:02:25.408
But I held it in.

01:02:29.787 --> 01:02:31.539
Didn't I do a good job, Mom?

01:02:32.331 --> 01:02:34.041
I'm a pro, aren't I?

01:02:34.125 --> 01:02:35.418
Ms. Dam.

01:02:35.501 --> 01:02:36.836
Are you drunk?

01:02:36.919 --> 01:02:37.879
But…

01:02:39.881 --> 01:02:41.382
today…

01:02:44.927 --> 01:02:46.304
I guess I was pretty stressed.

01:02:48.014 --> 01:02:51.017
I took my anger out on Dad for no reason.

01:02:51.100 --> 01:02:52.643
Hang up before you embarrass yourself.

01:02:52.727 --> 01:02:53.936
I'm pathetic,

01:02:54.687 --> 01:02:55.897
aren't I?

01:02:55.980 --> 01:02:57.523
I'm hanging up.

01:02:59.984 --> 01:03:01.152
Hello?

01:03:01.235 --> 01:03:03.112
Ms. Dam!

01:03:13.080 --> 01:03:15.124
The person you are calling is unavailable.

01:03:27.261 --> 01:03:28.346
Mom…

01:03:31.307 --> 01:03:32.809
I miss you,

01:03:34.018 --> 01:03:35.269
Mom.

01:03:54.580 --> 01:03:55.581
I'm bleeding.

01:04:25.278 --> 01:04:29.198
SCHOOL ZONE

01:04:45.548 --> 01:04:48.426
CONVENIENCE STORE

01:05:48.569 --> 01:05:50.363
SOLD OUT ON YOU

01:05:50.446 --> 01:05:56.369
THANKS TO SPECIAL GUEST AHN SANG-WOO

01:06:20.518 --> 01:06:22.520
Are you curious whether she slept well

01:06:22.603 --> 01:06:26.148
or if she made sure to eat her meals?

01:06:26.232 --> 01:06:28.109
Are talks going smoothly
with Gojeuneok Bio?

01:06:28.192 --> 01:06:30.027
It's been a long time, Mr. Lee.

01:06:30.111 --> 01:06:33.114
Whatever you do,
nothing's going to change.

01:06:33.197 --> 01:06:35.074
He won't buy the corn?

01:06:35.157 --> 01:06:38.536
All this corn might go to waste.

01:06:38.619 --> 01:06:39.912
This has nothing to do with you.

01:06:39.996 --> 01:06:41.038
-Let's sell them.
-What?

01:06:41.122 --> 01:06:43.749
Let's sell them through a livestream.

01:06:43.833 --> 01:06:46.752
Hello, everyone.
I'm home shopping host Dam Ye-jin.

01:06:46.836 --> 01:06:49.255
Ms. Dam, stay still.

01:06:57.930 --> 01:06:59.932
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
